To be given to M}{\plain \fs24 \super rs}{\plain \fs24  Arthur Severn in event of my death / AW.,  so they must have been for some time in \softline
the possession of Alexander Wedderburn. Brief descriptions of volumes 2-6 follow. (I have not \softline
compared the volumes{\u8217\'92} contents, letter by letter, against editions of the letters in question, and I have \softline
not attempted to be thorough regarding publication history. Many of the letters in these volumes, of \softline
course, were first published in }{\plain \fs24 \ul Works}{\plain \fs24 ; Collingwood, }{\plain \fs24 \ul Life}{\plain \fs24 ; and Cook, }{\plain \fs24 \ul Life}{\plain \fs24 ):\par
